Ringier in Talks to Buy Minority Stake in Nepszabadsag, MTI Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-12-01T14:59:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/ringier-in-talks-to-buy-minority-stake-in-nepszabadsag-mti-says.html
Switzerland ’s Ringier AG is in talks
to buy out the minority stakes in  Nepszabadsag  newspaper,  MTI 
reported, citing Attila Mihok, the managing director of
Ringier’s Hungarian unit.  Ringier owns 70 percent of Nepszabadsag, while Szabad Sajto
Alapitvany, a foundation, owns 27.7 percent and the newspaper’s
journalists own 2 percent, the state news service reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  